    "Figure 9 presents cases where both the baseline method (Standard Prompt) and the proposed TIP framework fail to generate satisfactory explanations, offering insights into their respective limitations.",
    "For the statement \"The black owl is red,\" the baseline method identifies that owls are not typically red, but it fails to address the key contradiction between \"black\" and \"red\" in the statement, resulting in a shallow explanation.",
    "In contrast, the TIP framework captures the contradiction between \"black\" and \"red,\" which is an improvement.",
    "However, it introduces an error by incorrectly stating that owls are typically \"white,\" overgeneralizing implicit knowledge and reducing explanation precision.For the statement \"The primary school did not accept members under the age of forty,\" the baseline method fails to recognize the nonsensical nature of the age restriction and does not address the contradiction.",
    "The TIP framework provides an explanation that claims primary schools accept students of all ages, which is inaccurate and irrelevant to the actual contradiction."
